title: Firefox lost all of my bookmarks - now what?
content:
Once upon a time, I had a home and multiple computers.

I used Firefox and everything was synced between computers - initially, through that separate program they used to use (I can't remember the name), but then it changed to some in-house Mozilla thing.

I lost my home last summer (due to a local bureaucratic issue that became a nightmare for several years - I was disabled and unemployed, but still had money to pay my bills) and was homeless for 5 months.

My desktop was stored, and my laptop thrown out (because it had some dead keys, and the screen was pretty shitty).

Several months ago, a friend gave me his old laptop. I downloaded Firefox and logged into my old profile. I think I was able to access my old bookmarks and passwords at that time.

Eventually, I found a new place to live. I still haven't set up my old desktop. I've been using my phone for essentials. Using my new used laptop recently, I find that, even though I'm logged into my Firefox profile, there are no bookmarks. Going into "sync", I see that "bookmarks" is *unchecked* - a change I never made.

Anyway - how do I find my bookmarks? Are they gone forever? If I get my desktop computer up and running, will they still be on that incarnation of Firefox, or are they now gone forever?
creator: electron.effigy
